provenance is never claimed by the model but measured by deletion, so tally(code) is the multiset of every rstripped non-blank line, in which indentation is meaning and n copies of a line must survive n times, caused_by(root, node, baseline) returns two multisets and not their union, the lines the baseline had that the anchored regeneration lost, and the lines it invented that were never asked for, and project(code, caused), given the build and a map from each node's path to the multiset of lines that node caused, returns two maps keyed by line number as a string, the first giving every line the sorted list of paths that caused at least as many copies of it as the build contains, and the second holding only the lines that no path could claim outright though some path took a few of their copies away, which are ambiguous and are left unclaimed rather than guessed;
